    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>British gold coins originally valued at 20 shillings, one pound sterling, and issued first in 1489; 21-shilling and 30-shilling versions appeared from the 16th century.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
